                            <comment id="14190767" author="amuraru" created="Thu, 30 Oct 2014 20:27:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looking at the code it seems that once the remote zk peers lookup fails, the refresh ts is updated and the return list of RS peers is empty.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Next time org.apache.hadoop.hbase.replication.regionserver.ReplicationSinkManager does not retry the lookup on the next polling as the following condition is not met:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (endpoint.getLastRegionServerUpdate() &amp;gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.lastUpdateToPeers) {
      LOG.info(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Current list of sinks is out of date, updating&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);
      chooseSinks();
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A fix would be to force a refresh when the list of peers is empty:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (replicationPeers.getTimestampOfLastChangeToPeer(peerClusterId) &amp;gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.lastUpdateToPeers
            || sinks.isEmpty()) {
      LOG.info(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Current list of sinks is out of date or empty, updating&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);
      chooseSinks();
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note that this is not reproducing in 0.94 where it seems the refresh is happening in this case.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14190926" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Thu, 30 Oct 2014 22:05:08 +0000"  >&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
+    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (endpoint.getLastRegionServerUpdate() &amp;gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.lastUpdateToPeers || sinks.isEmpty()) {
+      LOG.info(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Current list of sinks is out of date or empty, updating&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It would helpful if the condition (list out of date or empty) is stated clearly in the log message.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14190960" author="lhofhansl" created="Thu, 30 Oct 2014 22:33:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;&quot;Current list of sinks is out of date or empty, updating&quot;&lt;/tt&gt; seems clear enough to me.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;+1 on patch.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;One thing we have to think through is what happens when the slave cluster is down for a bit. We&apos;d chose sinks again on each call. I think that&apos;s OK especially since we dialed down the retry interval to 5mins recently after a bit.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, we can still be a bad situation where RegionServers die and restart at the slave cluster, we could go down to a single RS at the peers before we try to choose sinks again. That&apos;s for another issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
